        <div id="MainContent_divOrigID" style="display: block; clear: both; padding: 10px; border: 0px solid red;">
         <b>
          <em>
           Excerpt from the official Academic Programs Catalog:
          </em>
         </b>
         <br/>
         <br/>
         <div class="tabledata1" id="MainContent_divDesc" style="padding-left: 10px;">
          Listed below are the approved requirements for the program from the official Academic Programs Catalog.
          <br/>
          Students must consult their advisors to learn which specific requirements apply to their degree programs.
          <br/>
          Following this section are the
          <a class="link" href="#DN">
           requirements as represented in Degree Navigator
          </a>
          , MSU's online advising tool. The Degree Navigator section is only available for programs using Degree Navigator for degree certification.
          <br>
           <br/>
           <div align="left" style="margin-left: 20px; background-color: #F5F5F5; border: 1px solid #666666; padding: 5px;">
            <div align="right" class="displaydata2" style="padding-bottom: 2px;">
             <a class="link" href="Text.aspx?Section=129#s7948">
              View this text within the context of the catalog.
             </a>
            </div>
            <br/>
            <div class="tablehead2" style="border: 0;">
             <span style="color: #333333">
              College of Social Science
              <br>
               Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science: Social Science Education
              </br>
             </span>
            </div>
            <div class="text" style="margin-left: 60px;">
             <p>
              The Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science: Social Science Educationprogram is a comprehensive teaching majorleading to the Bachelor of Arts degree in the College of Social Science. Itis available for teacher certification and is only available to students pursuing teacher certification. Students who complete the requirements for this major and the requirements for teacher certification are recommended for a secondary teaching certificate in social studies. Persons with teacher certification in social studies are qualified to teach history, political science, geography, and economics.
             </p>
             <p>
              <strong>
               Requirements for the Bachelor of Arts Degree in Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science: Social Science Education
              </strong>
             </p>
             <ol>
              <li>
               The University requirements for bachelors degrees as described in the
               <em>
                UndergraduateEducation
               </em>
               section of this catalog; 120 credits, including general elective credits, are required for the Bachelor of Arts degree in Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science: Social Science Education.
               <br/>
               The Universitys Tier II writing requirement for the Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science: Social Science Education major is met by completingHistory 480 or 481 or 482 or 483 or 483 or 485 or 486 or 487 or 488. Those courses are referenced in item 3. below.
              </li>
              <li>
               Students in the Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science: Social Science Education major are not required to complete the College of Social Science requirements referenced under the heading Graduation Requirements for the Bachelor of Arts and Bachelor of Science Degrees in the College of Social Science section of this catalog.
              </li>
              <li>
               The following requirements for the major:
              </li>
             </ol>

        <div id="MainContent_divDNBatch" style="display: block; clear: both; padding: 10px; border: 0px solid red;">
         <a name="DN">
          <b>
           <em>
            Degree Requirements from Degree Navigator.
           </em>
          </b>
         </a>
         <br/>
         <br/>
         <div class="tabledata1" id="MainContent_dnBatchDesc" style="padding-left: 10px;">
          <b>
           NOTE:
          </b>
          Degree Navigator is an advising tool only and should not be viewed as a contract with the student.  
                    Any questions about the requirements should be directed to an academic advisor.
          <br/>
          <br/>
         </div>
         <br/>
         <div id="MainContent_divDnData">
          <div align="left" style="margin-left: 20px; background-color: #F5F5F5; border: 1px solid #666666; padding: 5px;">
           <div align="right" class="displaydata2" style="padding-bottom: 2px;">
            <a class="link" href="http://degnav.msu.edu/">
             Proceed to Degree Navigator.
            </a>
           </div>
           <br/>
           <span class="tablehead2">
            Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science: Education, BA (7685)
           </span>
           <span class="tabledata1">
            Required Credits: 120Program Version: SS15
           </span>
           <br>
            <br>
             <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
              Requirement 1: University Tier I Writing
              <br/>
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
              University Tier I Writing: The required number of courses from 1 of the following sets of courses
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
              WRA: 1. WRA: 1 course from WRA110, WRA115, WRA120, WRA125, WRA130, WRA135, WRA140, WRA145, WRA150, WRA195H, LB133, AL192, AL192H
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
              James Madison Writing: 2. James Madison Writing: 2 courses from MC111, MC112
             </div>
             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
              Residential College Writing: 3. Residential College Writing: 2 courses from RCAH111, RCAH112
             </div>
             <br>
              <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
               Requirement 2: University Mathematics
               <br/>
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
               University Mathematics: The required number of courses from 1 of the following sets of courses
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
               MTH2: 1 course
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
               At least 1 course from LB118, MTH110, MTH116, MTHRQMT, MTHWAIV1, MTHWAIV2, Mathematics Pre-Matriculation, Mathematics Post-Matriculation
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
               MTH1: 2 courses
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
               At least 1 course from MTH103, MTH103WAIV
              </div>
              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
               At least 1 course from MTH112, MTH114, MTH124, MTH132, MTH152H, MTH201, STT200, STT201
              </div>
              <br>
               <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                Requirement 3: University IAH201 - IAH210
                <br/>
               </div>
               <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                University IAH201 - IAH210: 4 credits from IAH201, IAH202, IAH203, IAH204, IAH205, IAH206, IAH207, IAH208, IAH209, IAH210, RCAH201, ANY IAH BELOW 211
               </div>
               <br>
                <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                 Requirement 4: University IAH211 or higher
                 <br/>
                </div>
                <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                 University IAH211 or higher: 4 credits from IAH211A, IAH211B, IAH211C, IAH211D, IAH221A, IAH221B, IAH221C, IAH231A, IAH231B, IAH231C, IAH241A, IAH241B, IAH241C, IAH241D, IAH241E, IAH241F, RCAH202, TRANSFER IAH, ANY IAH211 OR HIGHER, approved LB courses
                </div>
                <br>
                 <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                  Requirement 5: University ISS200 Series
                  <br/>
                 </div>
                 <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                  University ISS200 Series: 4 credits from ISS210, ISS215, ISS220, ISS225, ISS230, ISS235, MC201, TRANSFER ISS 200 LEVEL, ANY ISS 200 LEVEL
                 </div>
                 <br>
                  <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                   Requirement 6: University ISS300 Series
                   <br/>
                  </div>
                  <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                   University ISS300 Series: 4 credits from ISS305, ISS308, ISS310, ISS315, ISS318, ISS320, ISS325, ISS327, ISS328, ISS330A, ISS330B, ISS330C, ISS335, ISS336, MC202, ANY ISS 300 LEVEL, approved LB courses
                  </div>
                  <br>
                   <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                    Requirement 7: University ISB
                    <br/>
                   </div>
                   <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                    University ISB: 3 credits from ISB200, ISB201, ISB202, ISB204, TRANSFER ISB, ISB ALTERNATIVE TRACK, ANY 3 CREDIT ISB COURSE
                   </div>
                   <br>
                    <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                     Requirement 8: University ISP
                     <br/>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                     University ISP: 3 credits from ISP203A, ISP203B, ISP205, ISP207, ISP209, ISP213H, ISP215, ISP217, ISP220, ISP221, TRANSFER ISP, ISP ALTERNATIVE TRACK, ANY 3 CREDIT ISP COURSE
                    </div>
                    <br>
                     <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                      Requirement 9: University Laboratory Experience
                      <br/>
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      University Laboratory Experience: The required number of credits from 1 of the following sets of courses
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      Univ Lab: 2 credits
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      At least 2 credits from ISB201L, ISB208L, ISP203L, ISP205L, ISP207L, ISP209L, ISP217L, ANY 2 CREDIT ISB/ISP LAB, LAB EXPERIENCE ALTERNATIVE TRACK, TRANSFER LAB
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      Alternative: 2 credits
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      At least 1 credit from ISB201L, ISB208L, ISP203L, ISP205L, ISP207L, ISP209L, ISP217L, ANY 2 CREDIT ISB/ISP LAB, LAB EXPERIENCE ALTERNATIVE TRACK, TRANSFER LAB
                     </div>
                     <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 140px; text-indent: -20px;">
                      At least 1 credit from an Alternative Track Lab credit
                     </div>
                     <br>
                      <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                       Requirement 10: University Diversity Distribution
                       <br/>
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       University Diversity Distribution: A total 2 courses
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       At least 1 course from NationalIAH or ISS courses emphasizing national diversity or both national diversity and international and multicultural diversity
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 100px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       At least 1 course from InternationalIAH or ISS courses emphasizing international and multicultural diversity or both national diversity and international and multicultural diversity
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 45px;">
                       Conditions:
                       <br/>
                      </div>
                      <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 80px; text-indent: -20px;">
                       University Diversity Distribution: No more than 1 course from IAH or ISS emphasizing both national diversity and international and multicultural diversity in Requirement(s) 10
                      </div>
                      <br>
                       <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                        Requirement 11: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Economics
                        <br/>
                       </div>
                       <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                        Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Economics: 2 courses from EC201, EC202
                       </div>
                       <br>
                        <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                         Requirement 12: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Geography
                         <br/>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                         Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Geography: 3 courses from GEO204, GEO221, GEO330
                        </div>
                        <br>
                         <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                          Requirement 13: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - World History
                          <br/>
                         </div>
                         <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                          Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - World History: 2 courses from HST140, HST150
                         </div>
                         <br>
                          <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                           Requirement 14: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - U.S. History
                           <br/>
                          </div>
                          <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                           Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - U.S. History: 3 courses from HST201, HST202, HST203
                          </div>
                          <br>
                           <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                            Requirement 15: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Michigan History
                            <br/>
                           </div>
                           <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                            Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Michigan History: 1 course from HST320
                           </div>
                           <br>
                            <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                             Requirement 16: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Political Science
                             <br/>
                            </div>
                            <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                             Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Political Science: 2 courses from PLS100, PLS140
                            </div>
                            <br>
                             <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                              Requirement 17: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - History Elective
                              <br/>
                             </div>
                             <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                              Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - History Elective: 1 course from HST310, HST311, HST312, HST313, HST314, HST327, HST378, HST379
                             </div>
                             <br>
                              <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                               Requirement 18: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - PLS Elective
                               <br/>
                              </div>
                              <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                               Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - PLS Elective: 1 course from PLS313, PLS320, PLS321, PLS324, PLS325
                              </div>
                              <br>
                               <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                Requirement 19: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Tier II Writing
                                <br/>
                               </div>
                               <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Tier II Writing: 1 course from HST480, HST481, HST482, HST483, HST484, HST485, HST486, HST487, HST488
                               </div>
                               <br>
                                <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                 Requirement 20: Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Teacher Certification
                                 <br/>
                                </div>
                                <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                 Major - Interdisciplinary Studies in Social Science - Education - Teacher Certification: 6 courses from TE150, TE250, TE302, TE407, TE408, TE409
                                </div>
                                <br>
                                 <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                  Requirement 21: Electives
                                  <br/>
                                 </div>
                                 <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                  Electives: 0 credits from Electives at Michigan State University and transfer coursework.  This number can change based on the credits of the coursework taken to fulfill University, College, and Major requirements.  Please contact your academic advisor with any questions.
                                 </div>
                                 <br>
                                  <div class="tableheading" style="padding-left: 10px;">
                                   Requirement 22: University Residency
                                   <br/>
                                  </div>
                                  <div class="tabledata1" style="padding-left: 60px; text-indent: -20px;">
                                   University Residency: 30 credits from MSU coursework, 27 credits from MSU courses taken after reaching junior standing, 20 credits from courses offered by MSU while admitted to major &amp; 20 of the last 30 credits must be MSU courses.  Please see academic advisor.
                                  </div>
                                 </br>
                                </br>
                               </br>
                              </br>
                             </br>
